To prove statements using unions (∪) can be done in Waterproof using `It holds that ...`, `It suffices to show that ...` and `We conclude that ...`.
All of these use the following equivalence.

$x ∈ A ∪ B ↔ x ∈ A ∨ x ∈ B$

Note this is similar to intersection, but instead of conjunctions (and), it uses disjunctions (or).
Below are exercises using unions.

